# Harness Workflow

- Start substantial work from `.llm/harness/workflow/activation.md`; keep run artifacts under
  `.llm/runs/<run-id>/`.
- Use `.llm/harness/workflow/run-loop.md` for the design checkpoint, implementation loop,
  validation notes, and handoff.
- For multi-branch work, follow `.llm/harness/workflow/supervisor.md`: each group gets its own
  branch, nested run directory, separate evaluator, and `--no-ff` merge.
- Use `.llm/harness/workflow/escalation.md` when scope changes, a gate cannot run, or accepted
  debt is required.
- Record architecture debt with `.llm/harness/templates/debt-entry.md`; do not hide doctrine
  violations in prose-only docs.
